  <label class="quiz-option"><input type="radio" name="u09-q3" value="0"> Convergent — each premise independently supports the conclusion.</label>
  <label class="quiz-option"><input type="radio" name="u09-q3" value="1"> Serial — the conclusion of one step becomes the premise of the next.</label>
  <label class="quiz-option"><input type="radio" name="u09-q3" value="2"> Convergent — each conditional is an independent reason.</label>
  <label class="quiz-option"><input type="radio" name="u09-q3" value="3"> Neither — the argument is invalid and has no structure.</label>
{% endcall %}

